---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Resume · Josh Belzman"
  description="Director of Analytics. 15+ years across MSNBC, CNN, Fred Hutch, Courier Newsroom, Eli Lilly, and Dick's Sporting Goods."
>
  <div class="page resume-page">
    <header class="resume-header">
      <div class="resume-headline">
        <p class="eyebrow">Resume</p>
        <h1>Josh Belzman</h1>
        <p class="resume-sub">
          Analytics, Measurement &amp; Product Leader<br />
          <span class="mono dim">Insights · Impact · Delivery · Innovation with Purpose</span>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="resume-actions">
        <a href="/Josh_Belzman_Resume.pdf" class="btn btn-primary" download>
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="14" height="14" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M12 3 V15 M6 11 L12 17 L18 11 M4 21 H20" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" fill="none" />
          </svg>
          Download PDF
        </a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <dl class="contact-strip mono">
      <div>
        <dt>Location</dt>
        <dd>Savannah, GA</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>Email</dt>
        <dd><a href="mailto:josh@belzy.net">josh@belzy.net</a></dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>Phone</dt>
        <dd>206.355.4447</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>LinkedIn</dt>
        <dd><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jbelzman" rel="noopener">linkedin.com/in/jbelzman</a></dd>
      </div>
    </dl>

    <section class="resume-section">
      <h2 class="resume-h2"><span class="resume-num mono">01</span> Summary</h2>
      <p class="prose resume-summary">
        Measurement leader who ships and scales. 15+ years owning delivery on
        dashboards, reporting frameworks, content strategy systems, and decision
        platforms. Able to translate messy specs into crisp requirements, MVPs,
        and tools that actually get used to answer business questions. Adept at
        turning AI tools into a force multiplier without sacrificing quality,
        data privacy, or human insight.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="resume-section">
      <h2 class="resume-h2"><span class="resume-num mono">02</span> Core Competencies</h2>
      <div class="competency-grid">
        <ul>
          <li>Discovery &amp; Insights</li>
          <li>MVP Scoping &amp; Delivery</li>
          <li>Engineering Partnership &amp; Spec Writing</li>
          <li>Stakeholder Collaboration &amp; Action</li>
          <li>AI-Native Workflows (LLMs, Copilots)</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
          <li>Roadmap Definition &amp; Prioritization</li>
          <li>Cross-Functional Facilitation</li>
          <li>Success Metrics &amp; Post-Launch Iteration</li>
          <li>Coaching &amp; Mentoring</li>
          <li>Data-Driven Decision Making</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="resume-section">
      <h2 class="resume-h2"><span class="resume-num mono">03</span> Experience</h2>

      <article class="role">
        <header class="role-head">
          <div>
            <h3 class="role-title">Director of Analytics</h3>
            <p class="role-org">Publicis Media &mdash; Dick&rsquo;s Sporting Goods</p>
          </div>
          <p class="role-date mono">Apr 2024 &mdash; Present</p>
        </header>
        <ul class="role-bullets">
          <li>Own client-facing Power BI reporting product end-to-end for a <strong>$300M+</strong> media program &mdash; discovery with strategy, investment, and client stakeholders; requirements writing; engineering partnership; roadmap of feature requests, fixes, and capability expansion.</li>
          <li>Designed tiered reporting framework (pacing, pulse, wrap) with defined scope, SLAs, and quality bars &mdash; operationalizing data storytelling at scale.</li>
          <li>Translate fragmented data (ad servers, CRM, social listening, IAS / DoubleVerify / DISQO, MMM, lagging outcomes) into a unified insight engine.</li>
          <li>Lead a four-person team using Agile workflows &mdash; sprint planning, requirements tickets, clear ownership lanes, cross-functional facilitation.</li>
          <li>Use AI tools as a force multiplier &mdash; added <strong>1&ndash;2 FTE worth</strong> of analytic and data-engineering capacity using LLMs and agents for ETL, spec drafting, requirements synthesis, taxonomy fixes, and prototyping. Serve on multiple agency AI task forces.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="role">
        <header class="role-head">
          <div>
            <h3 class="role-title">Associate Director of Analytics</h3>
            <p class="role-org">Zenith Media &mdash; Eli Lilly &amp; Co.</p>
          </div>
          <p class="role-date mono">Mar 2022 &mdash; Apr 2024</p>
        </header>
        <ul class="role-bullets">
          <li>Shipped a Power BI reporting product covering <strong>8 pharmaceutical brands</strong> &mdash; owned discovery with brand teams, defined scope, wrote requirements, leveraged DAX, ran UAT cycles, and managed the post-launch backlog.</li>
          <li>Built decision frameworks. Triangulated IQVIA Rx outcomes, MMM results, and leading digital media indicators into clear go/stop/monitor views &mdash; answering &ldquo;so what?&rdquo; and &ldquo;what next?&rdquo;</li>
          <li>Ran enablement and adoption programs to make sure the product got used the way it was designed.</li>
          <li>Introduced AI-assisted workflows &mdash; compressed manual reporting cycles and reallocated team capacity toward higher-value work.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="role">
        <header class="role-head">
          <div>
            <h3 class="role-title">Senior Analytics Manager</h3>
            <p class="role-org">Courier Newsroom</p>
          </div>
          <p class="role-date mono">Mar 2020 &mdash; Feb 2022</p>
        </header>
        <ul class="role-bullets">
          <li>Designed, built, flew the plane. Launched an end-to-end newsroom analytics product on GCP with virtually no budget &mdash; Looker dashboards tied to BigQuery, WordPress, Sprout Social, Mailchimp, and voter file data.</li>
          <li>Beat audience growth goals by tying content engagement directly to audience strategy.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="role">
        <header class="role-head">
          <div>
            <h3 class="role-title">Digital Analytics Consultant</h3>
            <p class="role-org">CNN</p>
          </div>
          <p class="role-date mono">Aug 2019 &mdash; Mar 2020</p>
        </header>
        <ul class="role-bullets">
          <li>Shipped DOMO dashboards for editorial and business teams. Standardized <strong>500+ visualizations</strong> to drive consistency and adoption.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="role">
        <header class="role-head">
          <div>
            <h3 class="role-title">Digital Engagement Director</h3>
            <p class="role-org">Fred Hutchinson Cancer Research Center · City of Seattle Mayor&rsquo;s Office</p>
          </div>
          <p class="role-date mono">Jul 2016 &mdash; Jul 2019</p>
        </header>
        <ul class="role-bullets">
          <li>Digital engagement and social media lead &mdash; content creation and strategy, measurement, vendor integrations, audience engagement.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="role">
        <header class="role-head">
          <div>
            <h3 class="role-title">Producer &amp; Systems Editor</h3>
            <p class="role-org">MSNBC.com / NBC News Digital</p>
          </div>
          <p class="role-date mono">2004 &mdash; 2016</p>
        </header>
        <ul class="role-bullets">
          <li>Guided editorial systems, content syndication tools, and early mobile/social distribution platforms on the #1 internet news site.</li>
          <li>Produced msnbc.com homepage, wrote and edited features, coordinated breaking news coverage, developed social media strategy and franchise plan.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="resume-section">
      <h2 class="resume-h2"><span class="resume-num mono">04</span> Tools &amp; Skills</h2>
      <dl class="tools-grid">
        <div>
          <dt class="eyebrow">Product &amp; Delivery</dt>
          <dd>Discovery &amp; customer interviews, requirements writing, MVP scoping, roadmap planning, Agile / sprint workflows, success metrics &amp; post-launch iteration</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt class="eyebrow">PM &amp; Collaboration</dt>
          <dd>Jira, Confluence, Airtable, Slack, Notion, Figma, Miro, FigJam</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt class="eyebrow">AI &amp; Automation</dt>
          <dd>Claude, OpenAI, Copilot, Gemini &mdash; daily use for drafting specs, customer research synthesis, prototyping, automating repetitive work; agentic workflow design</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt class="eyebrow">Data &amp; Technical</dt>
          <dd>SQL, Python (working level), Power BI, Tableau, Looker, DAX, BigQuery, Redshift, Snowflake</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </section>

    <section class="resume-section">
      <h2 class="resume-h2"><span class="resume-num mono">05</span> Education &amp; Certifications</h2>
      <ul class="resume-list">
        <li><strong>B.A., Journalism and English</strong> &mdash; University of Washington</li>
        <li>Microsoft Project Management Certification</li>
        <li>Certifications in AI Integration and Media Analytics</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .resume-page {
    padding-top: var(--s-8);
  }

  .resume-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: end;
    gap: var(--s-5);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: var(--s-6);
  }

  .resume-headline h1 {
    margin: var(--s-3) 0 var(--s-3);
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
  }

  .resume-sub {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--c-text-mute);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .resume-sub .dim {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--c-text-dim);
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: var(--s-2);
  }

  .contact-strip {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--s-4);
    padding: var(--s-5) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--c-border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-border);
    margin-bottom: var(--s-7);
  }

  .contact-strip dt {
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--c-text-dim);
    margin-bottom: var(--s-2);
  }

  .contact-strip dd {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--c-text);
  }

  .contact-strip a { color: var(--c-text); }
  .contact-strip a:hover { color: var(--c-accent-2); }

  .resume-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--s-8);
  }

  .resume-h2 {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--c-text-mute);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: var(--s-5);
    padding-bottom: var(--s-3);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-border);
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--s-3);
  }

  .resume-num {
    color: var(--c-accent);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .resume-summary {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--c-text);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: var(--w-prose);
  }

  .competency-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--s-5);
  }

  .competency-grid ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .competency-grid li {
    padding: var(--s-2) 0;
    color: var(--c-text);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--c-border);
    position: relative;
    padding-left: var(--s-5);
  }

  .competency-grid li::before {
    content: '▸';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--c-accent);
    font-family: var(--f-mono);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .competency-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0; }
  }

  .role {
    padding: var(--s-5) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-border);
  }

  .role:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }

  .role-head {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--s-4);
    margin-bottom: var(--s-4);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .role-title {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 var(--s-1);
    color: var(--c-text);
  }

  .role-org {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--c-accent-2);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
  }

  .role-date {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--c-text-mute);
    margin: 0;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .role-bullets {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .role-bullets li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: var(--s-5);
    margin-bottom: var(--s-3);
    color: var(--c-text);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .role-bullets li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    color: var(--c-accent);
    font-family: var(--f-mono);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .role-bullets strong { color: var(--c-text); font-weight: 600; }

  .tools-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--s-5);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .tools-grid div { padding: 0; margin: 0; }

  .tools-grid dt { margin-bottom: var(--s-2); }
  .tools-grid dd {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--c-text);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .tools-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  .resume-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .resume-list li {
    padding: var(--s-2) 0;
    color: var(--c-text);
  }

  /* ---------- print styles ---------- */
  @media print {
    body::before, body::after { display: none; }
    body { background: white; color: black; }
    .site-header, .site-footer, .resume-actions { display: none !important; }
    .resume-page { padding-top: 0; }
    h1, h2, h3 { color: black; }
    .resume-h2 { color: black; border-color: black; }
    .role-org { color: #1E5BD8; }
    .role { break-inside: avoid; }
    a { color: black; text-decoration: underline; }
  }
</style>
